<plot>An ironic look at the way newspapers report childrens' deaths: accidents, bad mothers, angry fathers and the bogeyman. Based on the film maker's archive of newspaper clippings, these are terrible stories that make great copy. With an inventive mix of still photography and live action, the film sweeps around Britain to create a chilling comment on death, news reporting and the family.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?473628</url></doc>
